  "history": "The client has a longstanding pattern of feeling pressured to perform well and to manage social interactions successfully. They report consistently presenting a confident front and hiding their vulnerabilities, which suggests a learned strategy to avoid negative evaluation. A recent business failure has resulted in significant financial hardship, intensifying their stress. Instead of seeking support from family or friends, the client chose to take out a loan, indicating a preference for self-reliance and avoidance of perceived weakness. In social situations, the client actively diverts attention from their financial struggles, reinforcing their pattern of concealment.",
  "helpless_belief": [
    "I am helpless",
    "I am defective",
    "I am trapped"
  ],
  "unlovable_belief": [
    "I am unlovable",
    "I am bound to be abandoned",
    "I am bound to be rejected"
  ],
  "worthless_belief": [
    "I am worthless, waste"
  ],
  "intermediate_belief": "If I show any sign of vulnerability or ask for help, others will judge me as weak or incapable, so I must handle everything on my own to maintain respect. Admitting financial difficulty would mean I have failed, and I cannot let others see that side of me. It's safer to keep my struggles hidden and maintain a confident appearance, even if it feels isolating.",
  "intermediate_belief_depression": "If I can't solve my problems alone, it means I'm fundamentally inadequate and things will never get better. There's no point in reaching out because it will only confirm that I'm a failure in others' eyes.",
  "coping_strategies": "The client avoids disclosing their financial difficulties to family and friends, instead opting for self-reliant solutions such as taking out a loan. In social situations, they distract attention away from their struggles, maintaining a confident facade. These strategies temporarily reduce anxiety but reinforce isolation and prevent the client from accessing support.",
  "situation": "Took out a loan instead of asking family or friends for help. In social situations, acts to distract attention from financial difficulties.",
  "auto_thought": "If I tell anyone about my financial problems, they'll think less of me. I have to handle this myself or everyone will see I'm a failure.",
  "emotion": [
    "anxious",
